{"type":"message","id":"918cc4bc","parentId":"3e572032","timestamp":"2026-04-12T12:24:03.015Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the current state and MEMORY.md to give Khuowgn a clear list of next tasks.\n\nCurrent state:\n- 17 sessions total\n- 4 running sessions (group -5168104492, 2 cron sessions, main webchat)\n- 2 failed sessions: `prompt-optimizer:subagent:0eb3c914` and `code-reviewer:subagent:370ec3dd`\n- 3 cron jobs running: 5p Progress (QLHV group), 5p Progress DTLX (direct), Daily Briefing 5AM\n\nFrom MEMORY.md pending tasks:\n1. **Stitch MCP async polling** - wrapper với embedded key đã deploy, test lại sau khi gateway restart ổn định\n\n\n2. **Stitch `stitch-connect` skill** - cần update để dùng MCP wrapper thay vì OAuth\n\nI'm also reviewing what's completed: students page filter, cron jobs, duplicate Telegram tokens, and exposed tokens. The recent work shows the ecosystem infrastructure is mostly done with the 34-agent setup, openclaw2.json, and all agent configs in place.\n\nFrom the commit history, I've got the ahv-works review cycle wrapped up with backend, database, performance, and security all reviewed and done, though the code review hit a snag with a failed session.\n\nLooking at the next steps, there are two main items: testing the Stitch MCP async polling wrapper since it was deployed but the gateway restart wasn't stable, and updating the Stitch connect skill to use the MCP wrapper instead of OAuth. The ahv-works review cycle is complete except for that failed code review session that needs attention. I'm also noting the failed sessions—prompt-optimizer and code-reviewer subagents both failed, so those are worth investigating. For QLHV and DTLX, I need to figure out what the actual next tasks are beyond the pending items I already listed, since those projects seem to have some current activity but I'm not clear on what specific features or fixes are coming next.","thinkingSignature":"698c