{"type":"message","id":"a4241fee","parentId":"cd1cad9b","timestamp":"2026-04-12T14:03:01.198Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The FE `feat/database-master` already has `cbe45c6` (\"align stat card key with BE status_detail value\") which was committed on the same day as the BE fix. So the FE is already aligned with BE's dashboard stats key.\n\nNow, let me understand the situation:\n\n1. BE `feat/notification-migration` — major changes: notify service, 4-collection migration, controller logging\n2. FE `feat/database-master` — major changes: responsive R3, ViDateInput, dashboard rewrite\n\nThese are essentially two parallel feature branches:\n- BE focused on backend notification/notify infrastructure\n- FE focused on UI/UX improvements\n\nThey should be mergeable. The question is which to merge into which. Normally:\n\n\n- FE branch should be merged into BE branch (since BE is the main integration point)\n- OR both could be merged into develop\n\nThe BE has the notification migration docs that reference Phase 3, so I need to check if the migration has actually been executed or if it's still pending. Let me look at the migration docs to understand the current status.","thinkingSignature":"4bc8b156152dbe481ffcc9dc114d56a9b738cbb32fe4eb273e473bb4ba4fc48e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_duy8jlyhgn3s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be && cat docs/MIGRATION_NOTIFICATION_3COLLECTION.md 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_duy8jlyhgn3s_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be && cat docs/openspec/notification-migration-verification.md 2>/dev/null | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":418,"output":358,"cacheRead":43595,"cacheWrite":1627,"to