{"type":"message","id":"bacf319d","parentId":"0453af56","timestamp":"2026-04-12T14:03:10.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clearer picture:\n\n1. **Notification Migration Phase 3** — Already executed and verified on 2026-04-11. All counts match, referential integrity 100%. This is done.\n\n2. **BE `feat/notification-migration`** — Contains: notify service, 4-collection model, controller logging, dashboard stats fix.\n\n3. **FE `feat/database-master`** — Contains: responsive R3, ViDateInput, dashboard rewrite, stat card key alignment.\n\nBoth branches are feature branches derived from `origin/develop`. They seem compatible. The question is:\n\nShould we merge `feat/database-master` into `feat/notification-migration` (BE is the main integration point)?\n\n\nOr merge both into `develop`?\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, these are two independent feature branches:\n- BE has the notification backend work\n- FE has the UI/UX work\n\nThe most natural approach would be:\n1. Merge BE `feat/notification-migration` into `develop` (backend done)\n2. Merge FE `feat/database-master` into `develop` (frontend done)\n3. Then deploy both together\n\nBut since Lead wants me to sync them, I should:\n- Check if there's any API contract mismatch between FE and BE\n- Recommend the merge strategy\n\nLet me check the API changes between the branches to see if there are any breaking changes I need to account for.","thinkingSignature":"c036b9a93cf6829f346f9140fa3b5240b393861a9f9237151ab4cd58245c0fe8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jcrpnrs9csom_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be && git diff origin/develop..HEAD -- src/interface/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts 2>/dev/null | grep -A3 \"status_detail\\|counts\\|notification\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jcrpnrs9csom_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"