{"type":"message","id":"e3dd0a07","parentId":"2c219edc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:31:36.319Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_u8ubtuubrtb7_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose from 'mongoose';\nimport bluebird from 'bluebird';\nimport logger from '@common/logger';\nimport { env } from '@common/helpers/env.helper';\n\nmongoose.Promise = bluebird;\nif (env.LOG_LEVEL === 'debug' && env.LOG_OUTPUT_JSON) {\n    mongoose.set('debug', (collectionName: string, method: any, query: any) => {\n        logger.debug(`Mongoose: ${collectionName}.${method}`, {\n            stringData: JSON.stringify(query),\n        });\n    });\n} else {\n    mongoose.set('debug', true);\n}\n\n/**\n * Singleton Database client\n */\nexport class DatabaseAdapter {\n    async connect(): Promise<void> {\n        const maxRetries = 3;\n        const retryDelay = 10 * 60 * 1000;\n        const uriConnect = `${env.MONGODB_URI}/${env.MONGODB_NAME}`;\n\n        for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= maxRetries; attempt++) {\n            try {\n                logger.info(`MongoDB connect attempt ${attempt}/${maxRetries}`);\n\n                await mongoose.connect(uriConnect, {\n                    authSource: 'admin',\n                    user: env.MONGODB_USER,\n                    pass: env.MONGODB_PASSWORD,\n                    useNewUrlParser: true,\n                    useUnifiedTopology: true,\n                });\n\n                logger.info('Connect to MongoDB successfully!');\n                return;\n            } catch (error) {\n                logger.error(`Connect to MongoDB failed (attempt ${attempt})`, error);\n\n                if (attempt < maxRetries) {\n                    logger.info(`Retry in ${retryDelay / 60000} minutes...`);\n                    await new Promise((resolve) => {\n                        setTimeout(resolve, retryDelay);\n                    });\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        logger.error('MongoDB connection failed after maximum retries. Exiting...');\n    }\n\n    async disconnect(): Promise<void> {\n        try {\n            await mongoose.disconnect();\n            logger.info('Disconnect from mongodb successfully!');\n        } catch (error) {\n            logger.error('Disconnect from mongodb failed!', error);\n        }\n    }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":249,"aggregated":"import mongoose from 'mongoose';\nimport bluebird from 'bluebird';\nimport logger from '@common/logger';\nimport { env } from '@common/helpers/env.helper';\n\nmongoose.Promise = bluebird;\nif (env.LOG_LEVEL === 'debug' && env.LOG_OUTPUT_JSON) {\n    mongoose.set('debug', (collectionName: string, method: any, query: any) => {\n        logger.debug(`Mongoose: ${collectionName}.${method}`, {\n            stringData: JSON.stringify(query),\n        });\n    });\n} else {\n    mongoose.set('debug', true);\n}\n\n/**\n * Singleton Database client\n */\nexport class DatabaseAdapter {\n    async connect(): Promise<void> {\n        const maxRetries = 3;\n        const retryDelay = 10 * 60 * 1000;\n        const uriConnect = `${env.MONGODB_URI}/${env.MONGODB_NAME}`;\n\n        for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= maxRetries; attempt++) {\n            try {\n                logger.info(`MongoDB connect attempt ${attempt}/${maxRetries}`);\n\n                await mongoose.connect(uriConnect, {\n                    authSource: 'admin',\n                    user: env.MONGODB_USER,\n                    pass: env.MONGODB_PASSWORD,\n                    useNewUrlParser: true,\n                    useUnifiedTopology: true,\n                });\n\n                logger.info('Connect to MongoDB successfully!');\n                return;\n            } catch (error) {\n                logger.error(`Connect to MongoDB failed (attempt ${attempt})`, error);\n\n                if (attempt < maxRetries) {\n                    logger.info(`Retry in ${retryDelay / 60000} minutes...`);\n                    await new Promise((resolve) => {\n                        setTimeout(resolve, retryDelay);\n                    });\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        logger.error('MongoDB connection failed after maximum retries. Exiting...');\n    }\n\n    async disconnect(): Promise<void> {\n        try {\n            await mongoose.disconnect();\n            logger.info('Disconnect from mongodb successfully!');\n        } catch (error) {\n            logger.error('Disconnect from mongodb failed!', error);\n        }\n    }\n}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776137496312}}
{"type":"message","id":"457ee277","parentId":"e3dd0a07","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:31:47.191Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now! The connection uses `authSource: 'admin'` with `user` and `pass` from env. But I set them to `\"none\"` which are strings, not empty. And MongoDB is running without authentication, so providing credentials might cause the connection to fail.\n\nBut wait, earlier when I tested from node console, it connected fine. Let me check what the actual MONGODB_URI is:\n\n`${env.MONGODB_URI}/${env.MONGODB_NAME}` = `mongodb://localhost:27017/dtlx`\n\nBut the connect call also includes `authSource: 'admin'`, `user: env.MONGODB_USER`, `pass: env.MONGODB_PASSWORD`. With `MONGODB_USER=none` and `MONGODB_PASSWORD=none`, the connection string becomes:\n\n\n`mongodb://none:none@localhost:27017/dtlx?authSource=admin`\n\nSince MongoDB isn't running with auth, these credentials cause authentication failures, though the direct test without credentials worked fine. I need to remove the credentials from the connection call.","thinkingSignature":"5b54163139131e3652da0d178509905c73985e3ec4773aaecda34b282bff5fea"},{"type":"text","text":"MongoDB credentials mismatch. Fix connection:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nl4zs9hx7zy9_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/common/infrastructure/database.adapter.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"                await mongoose.connect(uriConnect, {\n                    authSource: 'admin',\n                    user: env.MONGODB_USER,\n                    pass: env.MONGODB_PASSWORD,\n                    useNewUrlParser: true,\n                    useUnifiedTopology: true,\n                });","newText":"                const mongoOptions: any = {\n                    useNewUrlParser: true,\n                    useUnifiedTopology: true,\n                };\n                if (env.MONGODB_USER && env.MONGODB_PASSWORD) {\n                    mongoOptions.authSource = 'admin';\n                    mongoOptions.user = env.MONGODB_USER;\n                    mongoOptions.pass = env.MONGODB_PASSWORD;\n                }\n                await mongoose.connect(uriConnect, mongoOptions);"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":543,"output":469,"cacheRead":60856,"cacheWrite":175,"totalTokens":62043,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776137496330,"responseId":"062ce819b4f473abca07b928f9915c45"}}
