{"type":"message","id":"a1bcce14","parentId":"b91cbc0e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:33:11.561Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still getting \"Authentication failed\" even though I set `MONGODB_USER=none` and `MONGODB_PASSWORD=none`. But my fix was supposed to skip those if they're empty... Let me check if the .env file was picked up properly. Oh wait, the server already started and printed \"Server is running on port 5555!\" before the auth error. \n\nWait - it printed \"Server is running on port 5555!\" and \"The api was started successfully!\" and THEN it got the auth error. This is strange. The MongoDB connection must have succeeded initially (it printed \"MongoDB connect attempt 1/3\" and then the server started). But then the error shows up after.\n \nI'm realizing the timing doesn't add up - if auth failed, the server shouldn't have started successfully at all. Maybe the startup code doesn't actually wait for the database connection to complete before printing that message, or perhaps there's a background connection attempt happening after the initial startup. The issue is likely that Mongoose v6+ has buffering enabled by default, so operations queue up and only fail when the connection actually times out, which is why the server starts successfully but subsequent queries fail. I should disable buffering with `bufferCommands: false` to get immediate connection errors instead.\n\nLooking at the env helper, it seems `MONGODB_USER` is returning a value even though I set it to \"none\" - the problem is that my null check doesn't account for a string value like \"none\" that should probably be treated as empty. So when the .env has `MONGODB_USER=none`, `getEnv` returns the string `\"none\"` which is truthy, so the credentials get added to the connection string even though they're not valid. The real problem is that the server prints success before the MongoDB connection actually fails, and then it retries after 10 minutes. I should either use empty strings in the .env file instead of \"none\", or fix the env helper to treat \"none\" as empty.","thinkingSignature":"7cb7afbbccc36475f412996736a65c60a050a72e9d5a87dbf122435a0ecae837"},{"type":"text","text":"Auth credentials vẫn được gửi. Fix env:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kkftxvl2h6m6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend && sed -i 's/^MONGODB_USER=none$/MONGODB_USER=/' .env && sed -i 's/^MONGODB_PASSWORD=none$/MONGODB_PASSWORD=/' .env && grep \"MONGODB_\" .env"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1179,"output":530,"cacheRead":61992,"cacheWrite":248,"totalTokens":63949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776137573718,"responseId":"062ce867c1c8a218b46f5e66da33b96e"}}
