{"type":"message","id":"3175543b","parentId":"c2a609eb","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:51:05.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log confirms:\n1. Auth IS working - AuthService decodes the JWT and gets `admin` role\n2. But then returns 404 for every protected route\n\nThe key insight: the JWT is being decoded successfully (AuthService runs), the user is found, the role is `admin`... and then 404.\n\nThis means the issue is that after `authMiddleware.auth()` passes, the routes in `systemRoutes`, `educationRoutes`, etc. are NOT matching the paths. But the dist/index.js clearly shows:\n```js\nrouter.use(system_route_1.default);\n```\n\nWhich means requests should be routed to system.route AFTER the auth middleware. But somehow they're returning 404.\n \nSo either the routes in those sub-modules aren't matching the expected paths, or the request is hitting the wildcard catch-all before it even gets there. Let me add some debug logging to trace exactly where the request is going.\n\nActually, wait - I think I found it. The system route's `/roles` path is registered with `listenNotify` as middleware, but `listenNotify` doesn't have a `path` property. When Express mounts a router with a path prefix, it strips that prefix before passing the request to the router's handlers. So if the inner router has `/roles`, it should correctly match `/api/v1/system/roles`. Let me check the actual dist files to see if the compiled code matches what I'm expecting.","thinkingSignature":"68917cc978f38eb68e7b03f6771bb49ff49a5ac3297c9e6f45dbd8031634e857"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9550nhom22zi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/ 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\" && grep -n \"router\\.\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/index.js | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider