{"type":"message","id":"3b97893a","parentId":"58590a31","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:52:42.602Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about this from a completely different angle. What if the issue is something very simple - like the running BE server was started from a different working directory or with different compiled files, and it has some issue with the route mounting?\n\nLet me try restarting the BE server with the current code and see if that helps. First let me kill the current BE server, rebuild, and restart.\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at the problem from the perspective of the `app.all('*')` handler being triggered. The request reaches `app.js:47` which is `app.all('*', ...)`. This means NO route matched.\n\nFor `/api/v1/system/roles`:\n\n\n- The main router has `app.use('/api/v1', api_1.default)` which matches the `/api/v1` prefix\n- The inner router mounts `system_route_1.default` directly at the root level, so `/system/roles` should match there\n- The `system.route.js` mounts at `/roles` and the roles router should handle the `GET /` endpoint\n- So the path should definitely match...\n\nUnless there's an issue with how the auth middleware is configured. I'm looking at the auth middleware setup and wondering if it's intercepting or blocking the request somehow, preventing it from reaching the routes downstream.\n\nActually, I think I need to restart the server and test with more detailed logging to see where exactly the request is getting lost. Let me kill the current running server and start fresh, then hit a known-good endpoint first to confirm basic connectivity before testing the problematic routes.","thinkingSignature":"3eab97ba29bcf1988a300195ad5e69f22e1b17e28e600632da5b4913c5381e05"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fhqcxw18dk7r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sv http://localhost:5555/api/v1/guests 2>&1 | grep -E \"HTTP|Location|< \" | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages",