{"type":"message","id":"563643e8","parentId":"96653e52","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:53:38.607Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the server IS running on PID 104486. The dist files were compiled at 03:34 today (after the TS errors were supposedly fixed in the previous session).\n\nLet me try a completely different debugging approach. Let me look at whether there's maybe an issue with how the `notification_dispatcher.listenNotify` is modifying the request or intercepting it somehow. Looking at the stack trace again - the `at param` functions are called. This is happening when Express processes route parameters. But `/api/v1/system/roles` has no parameters... unless the `listenNotify` is setting up something.\n\nWait actually - let me look at the `normalizeRoute` function more carefully. \n\nI'm examining the regex patterns used for different HTTP methods. For GET requests, the regex matches either an empty path with a trailing slash or a path with query parameters. Let me trace through what happens when `normalizeRoute` processes `/api/v1/system/roles` to see where the parameter handling might be going wrong.","thinkingSignature":"4582eba43a34ca15a2a5eaec36d37265645a5936c89415bf7e91b6377b93aad6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kqqd3nmqan03_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/common/notifications/notification.helper.js | grep -A20 \"function normalizeRoute\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":143,"output":267,"cacheRead":50214,"cacheWrite":935,"totalTokens":51559,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776138809981,"responseId":"062ced3be5047df5bc06b7051bf8105a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bae6ac4","parentId":"563643e8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:53:38.869Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kqqd3nmqan03_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"function normalizeRoute(route, method) {\n    const regex = {\n        POST: /\\/$/,\n        PATCH: /\\/[a-z0-9A-Z]+\\/?$/,\n        DELETE: /\\/[a-z0-9A-Z]+\\/?$/,\n        GET: /(\\/?\\?.*)|\\/$/,\n    };\n    return route.replace(regex[method], '');\n}\nexports.normalizeRoute = normalizeRoute;\nasync function getUsersFromConfigs(config) {\n    try {\n        const configUser = config.channel_config.allowed_users;\n        if (configUser.user_ids.length === 0 && configUser.roles.length === 0) {\n            return [];\n        }\n        const userIds = configUser.user_ids?.map((e) => String(e.id)) ?? [];\n        let roleName;\n        if (configUser.roles.length > 0) {\n            roleName = configUser.roles;\n            const uniqueRoles = [...new Set(roleName)];"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":48,"aggregated":"function normalizeRoute(route, method) {\n    const regex = {\n        POST: /\\/$/,\n        PATCH: /\\/[a-z0-9A-Z]+\\/?$/,\n        DELETE: /\\/[a-z0-9A-Z]+\\/?$/,\n        GET: /(\\/?\\?.*)|\\/$/,\n    };\n    return route.replace(regex[method], '');\n}\nexports.normalizeRoute = normalizeRoute;\nasync function getUsersFromConfigs(config) {\n    try {\n        const configUser = config.channel_config.allowed_users;\n        if (configUser.user_ids.length === 0 && configUser.roles.length === 0) {\n            return [];\n        }\n        const userIds = configUser.user_ids?.map((e) => String(e.id)) ?? [];\n        let roleName;\n        if (configUser.roles.length > 0) {\n            roleName = configUser.roles;\n            const uniqueRoles = [...new Set(roleName)];","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776138818860}}
{"type":"message","id":"59e19077","parentId":"1bae6ac4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:53:46.658Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK the `normalizeRoute` function looks fine. For GET `/api/v1/system/roles`, it would match the `/` at the end, so it strips the trailing `/`, returning `/api/v1/system/roles`. That's fine.\n\nLet me try yet another approach. The issue might be with how `authMiddleware.auth()` is being called. Let me look at the index.js more carefully:\n\n```js\nrouter.use(authMiddleware.auth());  // ← Note the ()\nrouter.use(system_route_1.default);\n```\n\n`authMiddleware.auth()` is called with no arguments, which means `...allowedFields` is `[]`. That's fine.\n\n\nNow I'm looking at the `auth()` middleware implementation - it's an async function wrapped in `catchAsync` that returns a promise, which should work fine. Let me trace through the `catchAsync` wrapper to see if there's something there that's causing issues.","thinkingSignature":"b814de288baab3d8b27309401c6406e50b55b5afd3c2bc9241928ecabfc362c8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6x219tihggqx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/common/utils/catchAsync.js 2>/dev/null || find /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist -name \"catchAsync.js\" | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":310,"output":273,"cacheRead":50921,"cacheWrite":541,"totalTokens":52045,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776138818875,"responseId":"062ced44a452fa5190e2a557cbf22d57"}}
