{"type":"message","id":"f5e50462","parentId":"004927df","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:53:59.133Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `catchAsync` utility looks correct - it wraps the async function and catches any rejections to pass to `next()`.\n\nLet me try yet another approach. Maybe the issue is that the running BE server (PID 104486) is somehow using OLD dist files that were compiled before the route fixes were applied. The dist was compiled at 03:34 today, which is AFTER the previous session's fixes. But maybe the fixes in the previous session didn't actually get compiled into the dist properly.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the previous session summary more carefully. The summary says \"Build succeeded after all fixes.\" But the BUILD was done in the PREVIOUS session, and the current server (PID 104486) was started AFTER that build. So the dist files SHOULD be correct.\n \nHmm, but there's something off here. Looking at the timestamps: the previous session's fixes were applied and the build completed successfully, but the running server was started in THIS session and is still on PID 104486. So either the server was started before the session compacted and is still running, or it was restarted more recently.\n\nLet me trace through what's happening with the auth middleware. The `auth()` function returns a middleware that wraps passport authentication in a promise, and I need to understand whether the promise is resolving correctly or if something's getting lost in that flow.\n\nLooking at the `verifyCallback`, it resolves the promise when authentication succeeds, which then triggers `next()` to move to the next middleware. So if the auth is passing and the token is valid, the flow should continue to `systemRoutes`. But if the token validation is failing silently somewhere, that would explain why the routes aren't being reached. I need to look more carefully at what `verifyCallback` is actually doing—specifically whether it's properly setting `req.user` and calling `resolve()` in all the right cases.","thinkingSignature":"eb94da8f5b42adf48bcf2ad16ade5f8feeaa735bb6ecb5347c0b7b6cd3f0d505"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4e1sh33nwgo0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,55p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/middlewares/auth.middleware.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":181,"output":443,"cacheRead":51190,"cacheWrite":758,"totalTokens":52572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776138826989,"responseId":"062ced4ca0583d0299606cd10d03a85c"}}
