{"type":"message","id":"364f6c25","parentId":"ce9b9920","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:54:12.084Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see it now. The `req.user` has `role_name` as a string (single value) in the JWT payload. But after the aggregation, it's being set to an ARRAY (`userRoles`). This is then used in `checkPermissions`:\n\n```js\nconst userRoles = getUserRoles.map((role) => role.role_name);\nreq.user.role_name = userRoles;\n```\n\nThis sets `role_name` to `['admin']` (an array). And in `checkPermissions`:\n```js\nif (!user.role_name?.includes('admin')) {\n    // ...forbidden\n}\n```\n\nSince `role_name` is `['admin']`, `'admin'.includes('admin')` would be... wait, `'admin'.includes is not a function! `'admin'` is a string, and strings have `.includes()`. \n\nActually, I'm second-guessing myself here. If `role_name` is already the array `['admin']`, then `role_name.includes('admin')` would correctly return true, so that check should pass fine.\n\nLet me step back and reconsider the whole flow. The JWT token is definitely being decoded and the user is being authenticated successfully, but the routes still return 404. Maybe the issue is that when the system router mounts sub-routes like `roles_route_1.default`, Express isn't properly routing requests to those mounted handlers. Or perhaps the problem lies with how the `listenNotify` middleware is intercepting requests before they reach the route handlers—specifically when it normalizes the route path.\n\nActually, I should check the `logTasks_service` import in the notification dispatcher to see if that's causing the issue when the route handler tries to access it.","thinkingSignature":"8bdd39ca965b21eec3f8c9491e12fde8371e885972b7744e27c3168c0fa04d2a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z2kaww03wjaj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there's a module resolution issue in the dist\ngrep -n \"logTasks_service\\|LogTasks\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/common/notifications/notification.dispatcher.js | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":677,"output":426,"cacheRead":51670,"cacheWrite":805,"totalTokens":53578,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776138839406,"responseId":"062ced58b2fa5369f914ac6a0fa3cc5b"}}
