{"type":"message","id":"bcd6b6c0","parentId":"edef089e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:54:23.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a completely different debugging approach. Let me look at what happens when a GET request is made by checking the actual flow.\n\nActually, I just realized something. Looking at the stack trace more carefully:\n\n```\nat Route.dispatch (/root/...express/lib/router/route.js:119:3)\nat Layer.handle [as handle_request] \n...\nat param (/root/.../express/lib/router/index.js:365:14)\nat param (/root/.../express/lib/router/index.js:376:14)\nat Function.process_params \nat Immediate._onImmediate\nat process.processImmediate\n```\n\nThere are 6 `at next` entries. \n\nThe param functions are being called twice, which means there are probably two route parameters being processed. I'm wondering if there's something about how the sub-routers are mounted that's causing the request to cycle through multiple handlers instead of reaching the final route. Let me add some debug logging directly to the running server to trace exactly where the request is going.\n\nActually, I'm going to take a different approach entirely. Since the previous session fixed the build errors and compiled successfully, but the running server might be using stale compiled files, let me restart the server to ensure it's running the latest code.","thinkingSignature":"edff6525d5b112391ffe90a7f410a9460ab355f918e1f370e3b9239f28f67a68"},{"type":"text","text":"BE đang chạy PID 104486 với dist đã compile lúc 03:34. Có vấn đề routing 404 dù auth pass. Thử restart BE với bản mới nhất:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jwkk4mc7ihrm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"kill 104486 2>/dev/null; sleep 1; ss -tlnp | grep 5555 || echo \"Port 5555 free\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":147,"output":360,"cacheRead":52027,"cacheWrite":1454,"totalTokens":53988,"cost":{"input