{"type":"message","id":"08cf69b9","parentId":"ecb76ff7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:58:25.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log in /tmp/dtlx-be.log shows the old server (the one that died with code 1 earlier when I ran `yarn dev`). But the current server (PID 106459) must be writing to a different log. Let me find its log.\n\nActually, looking at the `yarn dev` command:```bash\nyarn dev > /tmp/dtlx-be.log 2>&1 &\n```\n\nBut the PID 106459 was started with `node -r ts-node/register ...` NOT via yarn/nodemon. This means there was already a process running when I tried to restart.Wait, I killed PID 104486 earlier. And then `yarn dev` tried to start a new server. \n\nSo the current server (PID 106459) must have been spawned by nodemon during the yarn dev attempt, but it's using the compiled output in /dist instead of the source files. The log file shows nodemon started it with ts-node/register, but the process itself is actually running from the compiled JavaScript.","thinkingSignature":"8cb0bedeb30ee889f968a37f31e0a8cf7c90ce423232e873358dd95debc41384"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ng41dbxa0koe_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"kill 106459 2>/dev/null\nsleep 2\nss -tlnp | grep 5555 || echo \"Port clear\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":405,"output":265,"cacheRead":57351,"cacheWrite":321,"totalTokens":58342,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139095607,"responseId":"062cee58e9780dd5dc741f1241db60f3"}}
