{"type":"message","id":"00ece360","parentId":"914d6192","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:59:57.450Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The server is running `node dist/server.js` (not ts-node). That's the freshly compiled version. Let me check if maybe the dist/index.js is different from what I expect. Let me look at it more carefully with grep.Actually, let me try to debug this by adding some console.log directly to the dist file and see if they appear. But that would require modifying the dist and restarting the server. Let me try a different approach - add a temporary route to the dist file.Wait, actually let me think about this differently. The issue is that `/api/v1/system/roles` returns 404 even though it should be handled by the router. \n\nI'm wondering if the routes are being registered but then something's preventing them from matching, or maybe the router itself isn't being used at all. Let me add a debug route directly to the Express app and see if that gets hit.","thinkingSignature":"6f67f6ec1379d19f0740ff77c77745c55dba57dfe8528c4ce7417a256817dba8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qrf7jr37vrfv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/index.js | grep -n \"router\\|auth\\|system\\|education\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":127,"output":245,"cacheRead":59934,"cacheWrite":1246,"totalTokens":61552,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139190286,"responseId":"062ceeb7683938e16981e723f8c82c5d"}}
