{"type":"message","id":"20a603e8","parentId":"db493eb8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:00:27.754Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"VERY interesting! The guest endpoint works: `{\"status\":\"success\",\"message\":\"Truy vấn danh sách khách hàng thành công!\",\"data\":{\"data\":[],\"meta\":...}}`. \n\nBut `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` also returns 404! This endpoint is in `auth.route.ts`:```tsrouter.post('/auth/refetch-token', authController.refreshToken);```\n\nAnd `/api/v1/guests` works. The difference is:- `/api/v1/guests` → handled by `authRoutes` → `router.use('/guests', guestsRoute)` → works\n- `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` → handled by `authRoutes` → `router.post('/auth/refetch-token', ...)` → 404- `/api/v1/system/roles` → handled after `authMiddleware.auth()` → 404Wait, even `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` is returning 404! This is in the auth routes, which should be BEFORE the auth middleware. Let me look at the auth.route.ts again:```ts\n\n\nrouter.post('/auth/refetch-token', authController.refreshToken);\n```\n\nThis is at `/auth/refetch-token` in the auth router, which is mounted at `/api/v1` via `router.use(authRoutes)`. So the full path should be `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token`. That should definitely match, but it's returning 404 just like the protected routes. This suggests the problem isn't with auth middleware at all—something else is causing all these routes to fail.\n\nWait, I need to check if there's another `/auth` route somewhere else that's intercepting requests.","thinkingSignature":"5e486558ebcbe7141676d9e72fa0b9bd847a93cf619c537683da02a28cc1b8b4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9cg1iysejsl9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"router.*auth\\|/auth\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/presentation/api/ --include=\"*.ts\" | grep -v \"auth.route\\|auth.middleware\\|auth.controller\\|authValidation\\|auth.service\\|//\" | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-mes