{"type":"message","id":"1c0405c6","parentId":"df55f8dd","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:00:45.972Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The dist/auth.route.js looks correct. It has:\n- `router.post('/auth/signin', ...)` \n- `router.post('/auth/refetch-token', ...)`\n- `router.patch('/auth/change-password', ...)`\n- `router.use('/guests', ...)`\n- `router.use('/devices', ...)`\n\nAnd in dist/index.js:\n```jsrouter.use(auth_route_1.default);  // mounts at /api/v1/auth/...router.use(authMiddleware.auth());  // then auth...\nrouter.use(system_route_1.default);\n```\n\nSo `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` should match `router.post('/auth/refetch-token', ...)` in auth.route.js. \n\nBut `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` is returning 404 even though it's defined before the auth middleware in index.ts. Looking at the actual index.js file, `auth_route_1.default` is mounted at line 38, so `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` should definitely be caught there first. Something's off with how the routes are being registered or matched.\n\nActually, wait—the POST to `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` without a token would hit the auth middleware and return 401, not 404. The 404 means the route isn't matching at all. Let me verify what I'm actually sending in the request.","thinkingSignature":"a713af3077fbc327eb38e41fd887555e97a4b00977e928d23832d71eedbd8d19"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qvvywcysbdh8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sv -X POST http://localhost:5555/api/v1/auth/refetch-token -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" 2>&1 | grep -E \"HTTP|< |^{\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":704,"output":345,"cacheRead":62904,"cacheWrite":1448,"totalTokens":65401,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139237264,"responseId":"062ceee6728d7360f26e120f74ca64b0"}}
