{"type":"message","id":"56a34eb1","parentId":"fb828341","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:01:04.360Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`authMiddleware.auth()` is only called at line 40. There's no global `checkPermissions` in index.js.\n\nSo why is `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` returning 403?\n\nMaybe the issue is that the OLD server (PID 106459) is STILL running? But I killed it and confirmed port 5555 is free... wait, no, I started a NEW server (PID 106744) and confirmed it's listening.\n\nLet me check if maybe the new server has the updated dist files. The PID 106744 is the new server I started with `node dist/server.js`. Let me verify.\n\nActually, let me try hitting `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` again without a token to see what it returns:","thinkingSignature":"75e5cfd882f3c2d195313631d39992745b3458caf0c1698c89c0b40312069c2f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rb9atk5ddxvj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:5555/api/v1/auth/refetch-token -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('status'), d.get('message',''), d.get('err',{}).get('statusCode',''))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":139,"output":249,"cacheRead":64954,"cacheWrite":911,"totalTokens":66253,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139256234,"responseId":"062ceef9eb40f230f51fb015374d9e77"}}
