{"type":"message","id":"3121c624","parentId":"ed5ccc78","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:01:15.533Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"\"Phiên đăng nhập đã hết hạn. Vui lòng đăng nhập lại!\" - \"Login session has expired. Please log in again!\" With 403 Forbidden.This means:1. The request went through auth middleware (otherwise we'd get 404 or 401 \"Vui lòng đăng nhập\")2. Auth middleware passed (JWT was valid, user was found)3. But the `checkPermissions` returned 403 because the user doesn't have permission for this endpointWait, how is `checkPermissions` being called? Let me look at the `auth()` middleware:```js\nconst auth = (...allowedFields) => {    return catchAsync(async (req, res, next) => {\n        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {            passport.authenticate('jwt', { session: false }, verifyCallback(req, res, resolve, reject, allowedFields))(req, res, next);        })            .then(() => next())            .catch((err) => next(err));\n    });\n};```\n\nThe `auth()` middleware only calls `passport.authenticate` and then `next()`. It does NOT call `checkPermissions`. So `checkPermissions` is not called in the `auth()` middleware.Wait, but `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token` returns 403 \"Phiên đăng nhập đã hết hạn\". This message doesn't match `checkPermissions` which says \"Bạn không có quyền truy cập\". Let me search for where this error message is actually coming from.","thinkingSignature":"c6f8195b29430377402694ed838d77e0322cd7f7b81203c58756dc41301e52c0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m5xxd2sppemn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"Phiên đăng nhập đã hết hạn\\|hết hạn\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src --include=\"*.ts\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":146,"output":420,"cacheRead":65507,"cacheWrite":649,"totalTokens":66722,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cac