{"type":"message","id":"099e39ec","parentId":"b55c880a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:01:45.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! Now I can see the actual flow from the log:\n\nFor `/api/v1/auth/refetch-token`:\n```\n[AuthService]: {\"id\":\"69ddb8dcfb6bb89cbb59b553\",\"email\":\"admin2@gmail.com\",\"iat\":1776139167,\"exp\":1776225567}[admin\nGET /api/v1/auth/refetch-token 404 155.152 ms```\n\nSo the auth passes (JWT decoded, user found, role is `admin`). Then 404.For `/api/v1/system/roles`:\n```\n[AuthService]: {\"id\":\"69ddb8dcfb6bb89cbb59b553\",\"email\":\"admin2@gmail.com\",\"iat\":1776139167,\"exp\":1776225567}[admin\n\n\nGET /api/v1/system/roles 404 27.246 ms\n```\n\nSame pattern—auth succeeds and returns `admin`, but then 404. The `*` wildcard handler is catching these requests, which means the routes aren't actually matching. I'm wondering if there's something wrong with how the system router is set up or if the import isn't being resolved correctly.\n\nLet me check the dist/system.route.js file to see what's actually being exported and whether the router is properly initialized.","thinkingSignature":"cd940e727a45f4e309c78375e557ffa7592f51ecd54ca435eefb845544c46d41"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fdyyw8su3xdc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -25 /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/system.route.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1383,"output":317,"cacheRead":67154,"cacheWrite":507,"totalTokens":69361,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139294382,"responseId":"062cef1fb1789ecac266038036da74cc"}}
