{"type":"message","id":"359ab836","parentId":"f7fb6fe9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:05:18.801Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the DEBUG logs for the system route appear but AFTER the server is already running. That's because the system.route.js module is loaded after the initial debug logs from index.js. But the `[DEBUG system]` logs appear AFTER `[DEBUG] index router created`. That's strange.Wait, no. Looking at the log again:- `[DEBUG] index router created` (from index.js)- `[DEBUG] Adding auth middleware` (from index.js)- `[DEBUG] Adding system route` (from index.js)- `Server is running on port 5555!` (from server.js)- `[DEBUG system] router created` (from system.route.js - module loading)- `[DEBUG system] /roles mounted` (from system.route.js - module loading)This means the system.route.js is loaded AFTER the index router is created. That's expected - the modules are loaded in order of imports. But the debug messages appear in the log out of order due to async buffering. This is fine.Now let me test the API and see if the debug messages appear:","thinkingSignature":"3f7aca90279fd365a59c77ffb16de61d9fc1e34854fdcf644cf522dc7b6d4cce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hx14b5qz3csq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Seed admin2 first\nmongosh \"mongodb://localhost:27017/dtlx\" --quiet --eval \"\nconst r = db.roles.findOne({ role_name: 'admin' });\nif (!r) db.roles.insertOne({ role_name: 'admin', description: 'Administrator', permissions: [], created_at: new Date(), updated_at: new Date() });\nconst u = db.users.findOne({ username: 'admin2' });\nif (!u) {\n  const bcrypt = require('bcrypt');\n  const hash = '\\$2a\\$10\\$KSkB.TO7aNSOGCEwNFDry.6EXYsI/9iQMRVeoIRfFa5zXej8zQGBO';\n  db.users.insertOne({ username: 'admin2', email: 'admin2@gmail.com', password: hash, status: 'active', first_name: 'system', last_name: 'admin2', phone: '030000000001', gender: 'male', dob: new Date('1900-01-01'), address: '', identity_card: '00000000001', created_at: new Date(), updated_at: new Date() });\n  const ur = db.roles.findOne({ role_name: 'admin' });\n  const u2 = db.users.findOne({ username: 'admin2' });\n  db.userroles.insertOne({ user_id: u2._id, role_id: ur._id, created_at: new Date(), updated_at: new Date() });\n}\nprint('OK:', db.users.countDocuments(), 'users');\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":249,"output":571,"cacheRead":76219,"cacheWrite":237,"totalTokens":77276,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139505471,"responseId":"062ceff36defe1fdf319de01fdc3bdfa"}}
