{"type":"message","id":"d99edbc3","parentId":"8c63cf37","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:06:56.536Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `[DEBUG listenNotify]` log is NOT appearing! But the `[DEBUG auth]` is appearing.This means the `listenNotify` middleware (which is in the system route) is NEVER reached. Even though `authMiddleware.auth()` calls `next()`.\n\nWait, but `[DEBUG auth]` appears AFTER `admin` in the log. The `auth()` middleware is:1. passport authenticate (async)2. when passport calls verifyCallback → resolve()3. `.then(() => { console.log(\"[DEBUG auth] passport OK, calling next()\"); next(); })`4. express calls next handler\n\nThe `listenNotify` should be the next handler after `auth()`. But it's not being reached.This is very suspicious. \n\nSo the middleware order in index.js is: auth middleware first, then system routes. When `auth()` calls `next()`, it should pass control to the system route, which has `listenNotify` as its first handler. But `listenNotify` isn't firing at all. I'm wondering if `auth()` is somehow calling `next()` with an error instead of successfully, or if there's something about how Express is processing these middlewares that's preventing the chain from continuing. The auth middleware is definitely running and calling `next()` to pass control along, so the issue must be downstream in the system routes. Let me check what happens after that call to see where the request is getting lost.","thinkingSignature":"0f10b75ad5e57fe09af75cb0a62b34aefa0c3f816cb3f46dd54778cec1c08069"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t9qa1icsxfln_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Add debug BEFORE auth middleware to see if request reaches it\npython3 -c \"\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/index.js', 'r') as f:\n    c = f.read()\n# Replace the debug logging\nc = c.replace(\n    \\\"console.log(\\\\\\\"[DEBUG] Adding auth middleware\\\\\\\");\\\\nrouter.use(authMiddleware.auth());\\\",\n    \\\"console.log(\\\\\\\"[DEBUG] Adding auth middleware\\\\\\\");\\\\nconst authFn = authMiddleware.auth();\\\\nrouter.use((req, res, next) => { console.log(\\\\\\\"[DEBUG index] request path=\\\\\\\", req.path, \\\\\\\"baseUrl=\\\\\\\", req.baseUrl, \\\\\\\"originalUrl=\\\\\\\", req.originalUrl); next(); });\\\\nrouter.use(authFn);\\\"\n)\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/index.js', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(c)\nprint('Done')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":208,"output":537,"cacheRead":78168,"cacheWrite":370,"totalTokens":79283,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139600295,"responseId":"062cf051cdd8bfa4486ca991d9494e0f"}}
