{"type":"message","id":"0222e8da","parentId":"2e4b3a5a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:09:35.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Express 4.22.1. So it should be Express 4, not Express 5. In Express 4, `router.use('/roles', ...)` is a PATH for the middleware, not a prefix for routes inside the router. Routes inside are matched against the stripped path.Wait, but the debug shows `path=/system/roles` inside the system router. This is WRONG if Express 4 is stripping the prefix. Unless... the system router is NOT being mounted with a prefix.\n\nLet me look at the system.route.js imports in index.js more carefully:\n```js\nconst system_route_1 = __importDefault(require(\"./system.route\"));\n// ...\n\n\n```\n\nSo `system_route_1.default` is the exported router from system.route.js. And in index.js, it's mounted directly with `router.use(system_route_1.default)`. That means the system router is being mounted at the root level without any prefix applied to it.\n\nThe system router has a sub-router mounted at `'/roles'`, so a request to `/system/roles` should match that sub-router. But the debug output is showing `path=/system/roles`, which means the path isn't being stripped when it reaches the system router. This is odd because if the system router is mounted at root level in the index router, the path should be `/system/roles` going in, and Express should strip the matched prefix when dispatching to the sub-router.\n\nLet me check if there's a mismatch between the TypeScript source and what's actually running in the compiled JavaScript.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"217b14f8d53fed6634164a574b7373a925344f544cc6ce6a73f8a4216fb2c10e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pyn9e1u548vu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/index.js | grep -n \"system\\|router.use\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":118,"output":379,"cacheRead":80778,"cacheWrite":695,"totalTokens":81970,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139764490,"responseId":"062cf0f5c65494c016ae0c18d31bea39"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b97acd0f","parentId":"0222e8da","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:09:36.041Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pyn9e1u548vu_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"31:const system_route_1 = __importDefault(require(\"./system.route\"));\n39:router.use(auth_route_1.default);\n43:router.use((req, res, next) => { console.log(\"[DEBUG index] request path=\", req.path, \"baseUrl=\", req.baseUrl, \"originalUrl=\", req.originalUrl); next(); });\n44:router.use(authFn);\n45:console.log(\"[DEBUG] Adding system route\");\n46:router.use(system_route_1.default);\n47:router.use(education_route_1.default);\n48:router.use(operation_route_1.default);\n49:router.use(notification_route_1.default);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":254,"aggregated":"31:const system_route_1 = __importDefault(require(\"./system.route\"));\n39:router.use(auth_route_1.default);\n43:router.use((req, res, next) => { console.log(\"[DEBUG index] request path=\", req.path, \"baseUrl=\", req.baseUrl, \"originalUrl=\", req.originalUrl); next(); });\n44:router.use(authFn);\n45:console.log(\"[DEBUG] Adding system route\");\n46:router.use(system_route_1.default);\n47:router.use(education_route_1.default);\n48:router.use(operation_route_1.default);\n49:router.use(notification_route_1.default);","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776139776033}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c913e75","parentId":"b97acd0f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:09:44.260Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait! Line 46: `router.use(system_route_1.default)` - there's NO PATH PREFIX! The system route is mounted at the ROOT of the index router. So the system router handles `/system/roles` with `path=/system/roles` (no prefix stripping).\n\nNow inside the system router, the routes are:```jsrouter.use('/users', ...);router.use('/roles', ...);\nrouter.use('/user-role', ...);\nrouter.use('/agents', ...);router.use('/log-tasks', ...);```\n\nFor a request to `/system/roles`:\n1. Index router: strips `/api/v1`, passes `/system/roles` to system router2. \n\nThe system router receives the full path `/system/roles` and matches it against its registered routes. Since none of them start with `/system`, the match fails and Express moves on to the next middleware. That's why it falls through to the 404 handler - the system router can't find a matching route because it's looking for `/users`, `/roles`, etc., not `/system/*`.\n\nThe real issue is that `system.route.ts` needs to be mounted at the `/system` prefix in `index.ts` so the path gets stripped before the routes inside are matched. Currently it's being mounted at the root level, which means the system router never sees the `/system` part of the path.","thinkingSignature":"0f633ae0694aca306022f9340f88c3d2bccdc70ada7374cff69cd3ce85f7b8fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x2pxjftv9nto_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"router\\.\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/presentation/api/v1/index.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":243,"output":340,"cacheRead":80918,"cacheWrite":955,"totalTokens":82456,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139776055,"responseId":"062cf101ddb4ed