{"type":"message","id":"0579beee","parentId":"154227a9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:09:52.514Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"In the source `index.ts`, the routes are mounted without a prefix:\n```tsrouter.use(systemRoutes);router.use(educationRoutes);router.use(operationRoutes);\n```\n\nBut in `system.route.ts`, the sub-routes are defined with paths like `/users`, `/roles`, etc. So the system router handles `/users`, `/roles`, etc. at the ROOT of the API.\n\nThis means the full paths should be:- `/api/v1/system` → no direct route (system router handles `/users`, `/roles`, etc.)- `/api/v1/education` → no direct route (education router handles its own paths)- etc.\n\nBut wait, in the current system.route.ts, the paths are:- `/users` → `/api/v1/users`\n\n\n- `/roles` → `/api/v1/roles`\n- etc.\n\nSo the routes ARE accessible without `/system` in the path! Let me test `/api/v1/roles` directly to see if it works.","thinkingSignature":"f69cc54517b3563a5697539e536a29f25c38d874357a734b67c793318e67d8e7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ygqnykvxjulf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat /tmp/dtlx_token.txt)\ncurl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" http://localhost:5555/api/v1/roles | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('status'), d.get('message','')[:50])\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":158,"output":292,"cacheRead":81489,"cacheWrite":870,"totalTokens":82809,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139784556,"responseId":"062cf109afcc9e7764a68a8152bd0c57"}}
