{"type":"message","id":"f0dad66c","parentId":"852f9af0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:11:59.754Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the actual paths:- `/api/v1/roles` ✅ - `/api/v1/users` - in system.route: `router.use('/users', ...)` → `/api/v1/users` but returns 404. Why?- `/api/v1/teacher-infos` - in education.route: `router.use('/teacher-infos', listenNotify, teacherRoute)` → `/api/v1/teacher-infos` but returns 404\n- `/api/v1/notification/configs` - WRONG path! It's actually `/api/v1/notify-configs` (in notification.route.ts)Let me check why `/api/v1/users` returns 404. The system route has:```js\n\n\nrouter.use('/users', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, listenNotify, users_route_1.default);\n```\n\nSo `/api/v1/users` should match. But it's returning 404. The `checkPermissions` middleware could be the culprit - it might be checking if the user has the right permissions for that path and returning 403 instead of passing to the next handler. Let me trace through what the server log shows for this request to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"61a8caf046c6559fe73e3ce23b74a228081340c77312ee392ee6aba4a39b1b7e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hslceql36xiv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -20 /tmp/dtlx-be-debug.log | grep \"DEBUG\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1450,"output":278,"cacheRead":85709,"cacheWrite":952,"totalTokens":88389,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139907067,"responseId":"062cf1850722ce4229644cc8723142ff"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0bd7812f","parentId":"f0dad66c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:00.004Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hslceql36xiv_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=/vehicles url=/vehicles\n[DEBUG listenNotify] path= / baseUrl= /api/v1/vehicles\n[DEBUG index] request path= /notification/configs baseUrl= /api/v1 originalUrl= /api/v1/notification/configs\n[DEBUG auth] passport OK, calling next()\n[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=/notification/configs url=/notification/configs"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=/vehicles url=/vehicles\n[DEBUG listenNotify] path= / baseUrl= /api/v1/vehicles\n[DEBUG index] request path= /notification/configs baseUrl= /api/v1 originalUrl= /api/v1/notification/configs\n[DEBUG auth] passport OK, calling next()\n[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=/notification/configs url=/notification/configs","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776139919995}}
{"type":"message","id":"339971dd","parentId":"0bd7812f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:09.793Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the actual issue!\n\nLook at the debug output: `[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=/notification/configs url=/notification/configs`\n\nThe system.route is receiving `/notification/configs` but system.route.js only has routes for `/users`, `/roles`, `/agents`, etc. It does NOT have `/notification/configs`.\n\nWait, but `/notification/configs` should be in the notification.route, not the system.route. But the system.route is receiving it because the notification route is mounted AFTER the system route in index.js. \n\nExpress matches routes in order, and since the system route is registered first with a wildcard pattern that captures everything, it's intercepting requests meant for the notification route before Express gets a chance to try matching the notification route.\n\nThe solution is to mount the notification route with a prefix like `/notification` so Express only passes requests to it when that prefix is present, allowing other routes to match first without being caught by the wildcard.\n\nLooking back at the original structure, system.route.ts had routes prefixed with `/system/`, `/system/users`, etc., which would naturally prevent this collision. But somewhere in the clean architecture migration, those prefixes got stripped out. I'm checking the actual dist files to understand what the original configuration was supposed to be.","thinkingSignature":"e646a5666465826fbe31ffe11bb08ca74d0c99d77f24e0a80facacee05c68d6c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ab308512avxq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend && git log --oneline -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":204,"output":312,"cacheRead":86400,"cacheWrite":1892,"totalTokens":88808,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139920020,"responseId":"062cf191a16f2c0a8aae47dce0bd2ba8"}}
