{"type":"message","id":"54f81e7d","parentId":"53e5eb1a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:20.279Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bu7zeysi4b7z_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { Router } from 'express';\n\nimport authRoutes from './auth.route';\nimport systemRoutes from './system.route';\nimport educationRoutes from './education.route';\nimport operationRoutes from './operation.route';\nimport notificationRoutes from './notification.route';\n\nimport * as authMiddleware from '../../../middlewares/auth.middleware';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// === Public Routes (không yêu cầu authentication) ===\nrouter.use(authRoutes);\n\n// === Protected Routes (yêu cầu authentication) ===\nrouter.use(authMiddleware.auth());\n\nrouter.use(systemRoutes);\nrouter.use(educationRoutes);\nrouter.use(operationRoutes);\nrouter.use(notificationRoutes);\n\nexport default router;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":69,"aggregated":"import { Router } from 'express';\n\nimport authRoutes from './auth.route';\nimport systemRoutes from './system.route';\nimport educationRoutes from './education.route';\nimport operationRoutes from './operation.route';\nimport notificationRoutes from './notification.route';\n\nimport * as authMiddleware from '../../../middlewares/auth.middleware';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// === Public Routes (không yêu cầu authentication) ===\nrouter.use(authRoutes);\n\n// === Protected Routes (yêu cầu authentication) ===\nrouter.use(authMiddleware.auth());\n\nrouter.use(systemRoutes);\nrouter.use(educationRoutes);\nrouter.use(operationRoutes);\nrouter.use(notificationRoutes);\n\nexport default router;","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776139940271}}
{"type":"message","id":"c36351dd","parentId":"54f81e7d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:29.265Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The original index.ts also has the same structure: `router.use(systemRoutes)`, `router.use(educationRoutes)`, etc. without prefixes. So the routes in each route file have their own paths (like `/users`, `/roles`, `/courses`, etc.).\n\nThe issue is that routes in different route files might overlap or conflict because they're all at the same level without prefixes. \n\nBut actually, looking at the route files:\n- `system.route.ts`: `/users`, `/roles`, `/agents`, `/user-role`, `/log-tasks` \n- `education.route.ts`: `/courses`, `/lessons`, `/students`, `/teachers`, etc.\n\n\n- `operation.route.ts`: `/vehicles`, `/payments`, `/stadiums`, etc.\n- `notification.route.ts`: `/notify-contents`, `/notify-users`, `/notify-configs`, etc.\n\nThese are all unique paths, so there shouldn't be any conflicts. The problem must be something else.\n\nLooking at the debug logs more carefully, I notice the system.route is receiving `/notification/configs` when it should be going to the notification.route instead. This suggests the routes aren't being matched in the correct order or the paths are defined differently than I thought. Let me check the actual system.route.ts file to see what paths are really registered there.","thinkingSignature":"f1b4d664753dfa13e4592db18e9d0ba694afacea90a44ca5f9e22db3e96cc7cb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ecz6nsxev1xd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/system.route.js | grep \"router\\.\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":242,"output":324,"cacheRead":88861,"cacheWrite":243,"totalTokens":89670,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139940298,"resp