{"type":"message","id":"54504b9a","parentId":"c36351dd","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:29.522Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ecz6nsxev1xd_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"router.use((req, res, next) => { console.log(\"[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=\"+req.path+\" url=\"+req.url); next(); });\nrouter.use('/users', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, users_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/roles', notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, roles_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/user-role', notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, userRoles_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/agents', notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, agents_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/log-tasks', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, logTasks_route_1.default);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":51,"aggregated":"router.use((req, res, next) => { console.log(\"[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=\"+req.path+\" url=\"+req.url); next(); });\nrouter.use('/users', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, users_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/roles', notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, roles_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/user-role', notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, userRoles_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/agents', notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, agents_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/log-tasks', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, logTasks_route_1.default);","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776139949515}}
{"type":"message","id":"f725f3ca","parentId":"54504b9a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:43.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The system.route.js has:- `/users` → users_route\n- `/roles` → roles_route- `/user-role` → userRoles_route\n- `/agents` → agents_route\n- `/log-tasks` → logTasks_routeSo `/notification/configs` should NOT be in system.route. But the debug shows `path=/notification/configs url=/notification/configs` inside system.route.\n\nThis means:1. Request comes to `/api/v1/notification/configs`2. Index router strips `/api/v1`, passes `/notification/configs`3. Auth middleware passes4. \n\nNow I'm realizing Express 4 matches routes in registration order. The `system_route_1.default` is a Router object, and when mounted it only matches paths that its registered routes handle. But `router.use(path, router)` in Express 4 treats the router as middleware rather than a prefix—it should only pass requests to that router if the path matches, not intercept all requests. So why is system.route receiving `/notification/configs` when it only has routes for `/users`, `/roles`, `/agents`, `/user-role`, and `/log-tasks`?\n\nLooking at the debug output more carefully, the `path` shows `/notification/configs` inside system.route, which is definitely wrong. The notification routes are in a completely different file. I'm wondering if this is actually a compiled file from the TypeScript migration, or if there's something wrong with how the routes are being generated during the build process.\n\nLet me think through this differently. If system.route has `router.use('/users', ...)` and the index mounts it without a prefix, then `/api/v1/users` should work. But the debug shows the path is being set to `/notification/configs` when it shouldn't be. Maybe the issue is that the router isn't properly resetting its internal state between requests, causing path information to leak across different route handlers. I'm wondering if the middleware order in Express is causing the system routes to intercept requests before they reach the notification routes, or if the notification routes aren't properly mounted at all.","thinkingSignature":"e8067a48822926c5811b657ed26a9f8a44fef6e1dfaefdb9b898d771871a0f2b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fgtjnpduz5zt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/notification.route.js | grep \"router\\.\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":250,"output":484,"cacheRead":89012,"cacheWrite":561,"totalTokens":90307,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139949535,"responseId":"062cf1ae247ea56d55e588eab5b014f9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d8c92af4","parentId":"f725f3ca","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:43.694Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fgtjnpduz5zt_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"router.use('/notify-contents', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifyContents_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/notify-users', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifyUsers_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/notify-configs', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifyConfigs_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/notifies', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifies_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/conventions', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, conventions_route_1.default);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":101,"aggregated":"router.use('/notify-contents', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifyContents_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/notify-users', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifyUsers_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/notify-configs', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifyConfigs_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/notifies', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notifies_route_1.default);\nrouter.use('/conventions', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, conventions_route_1.default);","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776139963684}}
{"type":"message","id":"e32c4da6","parentId":"d8c92af4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:12:52.668Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The notification.route has `/notify-configs`, NOT `/notification/configs`. So `/api/v1/notification/configs` is wrong - the correct path is `/api/v1/notify-configs`.\n\nLet me now fix the actual issues:\n\n1. `/api/v1/users` - returns 404 → need to check why system.route doesn't match `/users`\n2. `/api/v1/teacher-infos` - returns 404 → need to check education.route\n3. `/api/v1/notify-configs` (not `/notification/configs`) - need to test\n\nLet me test with the correct path:","thinkingSignature":"29e5e81dfa469e17b85bfd84b657f0cc5ba7373e1d26dc4db07d4acf25f85f11"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hwy446gtty5y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat /tmp/dtlx_token.txt)\npython3 << PYEOF\nimport json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\ntoken = open(\"/tmp/dtlx_token.txt\").read().strip()\ntests = [\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/users\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/teacher-infos\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/notify-configs\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/students\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/courses\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/lessons\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/stadiums\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/payments\", True),\n]\n\nfor method, path, auth in tests:\n    try:\n        req = urllib.request.Request(f\"http://localhost:5555{path}\", method=method)\n        if auth:\n            req.add_header(\"Authorization\", f\"Bearer {token}\")\n        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5)\n        rd = json.loads(resp.read())\n        if isinstance(rd.get(\"data\"), list):\n            print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | {len(rd['data'])} items\")\n        elif isinstance(rd.get(\"data\"), dict):\n            d2 = rd[\"data\"]\n            if \"docs\" in d2: print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | {len(d2['docs'])} items\")\n            elif \"doc\" in d2: print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | 1 doc\")\n            else: print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | keys={list(d2.keys())[:5]}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status}\")\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        body = e.read().decode()[:100]\n        print(f\"❌ {path}: {e.code} → {body}\")\n    except Exception as ex:\n        print(f\"❌ {path}: {ex}\")\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":203,"output":582,"cacheRead":89244,"cacheWrite":966,"totalTokens":90995,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139963711,"responseId":"062cf1bd439db0abe43b4d39960a61bf"}}
