{"type":"message","id":"62446db4","parentId":"f00edd3e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:13:02.886Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the pattern more clearly:- Working (200): `/api/v1/notify-configs`, `/api/v1/courses`, `/api/v1/lessons`, `/api/v1/stadiums`, `/api/v1/payments`, `/api/v1/roles`, `/api/v1/agents`, `/api/v1/vehicles`- NOT working (404): `/api/v1/users`, `/api/v1/teacher-infos`, `/api/v1/students`\n\nThese are routes that are either:1. In the system.route but have `checkPermissions` before `listenNotify` (`/users`)2. In the education.route (`/teacher-infos`, `/students`)The ones that work are in the education.route (courses, lessons) and operation.route (vehicles, stadiums, payments). Let me check why `/teacher-infos` and `/students` don't work but `/courses` and `/lessons` do work.\n\n\nLooking at the education.route setup, `/courses` and `/lessons` are registered before the catch-all `router.use()` for `/courses`, but `/teacher-infos` comes after it. The ordering of these routes might be preventing the later ones from matching properly.","thinkingSignature":"a316f0d42c6b360be87013de113a3db782103dbf87fc5beb322cb08130b05d7b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jxrji0iygk8t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"router\\.\\|teacher-info\\|student\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/presentation/api/v1/education.route.js | grep -v \"import\\|DEBUG\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":320,"output":329,"cacheRead":89721,"cacheWrite":1177,"totalTokens":91547,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139973826,"responseId":"062cf1c70f4d8fd6b27c0028c4fbd750"}}
