{"type":"message","id":"57f8eb09","parentId":"b4a25df3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:13:14.202Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The education.route.js has:\n- Line 54: `router.post('/students/register', ...)` - POST only!\n- Line 55: `router.get('/students/:id', ...)` - GET by ID only!\n- Line 56: `router.get('/teachers/rankings', ...)` - GET rankings only!\n\nThere's NO `router.get('/students')` or `router.get('/teacher-infos')` or `router.use('/students', ...)` for listing!\n\nSo:\n- `/api/v1/students` → 404 (there's only POST `/students/register` and GET `/students/:id`)\n\n\n- `/api/v1/teacher-infos` → 404 (there's only GET `/teachers/rankings`)\n\nLooking at the test results, I can see the actual endpoints that work: `GET /api/v1/lessons` returns data with pagination metadata, while other endpoints like courses, stadiums, and payments return empty arrays. The `/lessons` endpoint must be accessible through the lessons router that's mounted at that path.\n\nThe 404 errors for `/api/v1/users` and `/api/v1/students` make sense now—`/users` is protected by `checkPermissions` middleware and might not be accessible, while `/students` doesn't have a direct GET endpoint since it's only set up for registration. I need to trace why `checkPermissions` is returning 404 instead of 403 for the users endpoint, since that would indicate a missing route rather than an authorization failure.","thinkingSignature":"eb7c0228a8ef1a727d17c634c71953c282327e3042f72a3e489588a156d38bea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3wa7qniqhzqc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what happens for /users in the log\ntail -30 /tmp/dtlx-be-debug.log | grep \"DEBUG\\|/users\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":583,"output":362,"cacheRead":90311,"cacheWrite":1139,"totalTokens":92395,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":