{"type":"message","id":"ce1f776d","parentId":"62ba8f6f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:13:32.300Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"NOW I can see the full flow for `/api/v1/users`:1. `[DEBUG index] request path= /users baseUrl= /api/v1 originalUrl= /api/v1/users` ✅\n2. `[DEBUG auth] passport OK, calling next()` ✅3. `[DEBUG system.route] ENTERED path=/users url=/users` ✅4. `[DEBUG listenNotify] path= / baseUrl= /api/v1/users` ✅\nThen 404. So the request goes through the auth, reaches the system.route, reaches the listenNotify for `/users`, and then... 404.\n\nWait! `listenNotify` is reached for `/users`. But system.route has:```jsrouter.use('/users', authMiddleware.checkPermissions, notification_dispatcher_1.listenNotify, users_route_1.default);```\n\n\nSo `/users` matches `router.use('/users', ...)` which chains `checkPermissions` → `listenNotify` → `users_route`. `listenNotify` is being reached, so `checkPermissions` must have passed too. But then 404 comes from `users_route`. Let me check what's happening inside `users.route.js`.","thinkingSignature":"34d4bce43ba39922462fd91c8ba5b8cd04ef0c919202dd64b9fc83e9ed7398de"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wekfd8u2b96x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"router\\.\\|router\\[\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/modules/users/users.route.js | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":192,"output":303,"cacheRead":91931,"cacheWrite":583,"totalTokens":93009,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776140004031,"responseId":"062cf1e6dccb0d6246bb22e7ab513bf6"}}
