{"type":"message","id":"086553a6","parentId":"ec497c24","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:13:52.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The `users.route.js` has:- `router.use('/teachers', ...)` → `/users/teachers`\n- `router.use('/students', ...)` → `/users/students`\n- `router.use('/sales', ...)` → `/users/sales`- `router.use('/leads', ...)` → `/users/leads`- `router.get('/role', ...)` → `/users/role`\n- `router.get('/:id', ...)` → `/users/:id`\n- `router.post('/', ...)` → POST `/users`\n\nThere's NO `router.get('/')` for listing all users! So `/api/v1/users` (GET) returns 404 because there's no GET handler for `/users`.\n\n\nNow I'm getting a clearer picture of the actual API structure. Looking at the test results, most endpoints are returning 200 with either empty arrays or proper response keys like `data` and `meta`. The working endpoints include `/api/v1/users/role` for listing, `/api/v1/students` (which is actually `/users/students`), `/api/v1/teacher-infos` (which is `/users/teachers`), and `/api/v1/notify-configs`.\n\nBut there are three endpoints returning 404s that I need to investigate. The `/api/v1/users` endpoint is likely missing a GET handler, and `/api/v1/teacher-infos` probably doesn't have a corresponding route either. Let me verify these by checking the actual test responses more carefully.\n\nLooking at the routes, I see that `/api/v1/students` is served by `students.route` which only has POST for registration and GET by ID, so a general GET request would 404. Similarly, `/api/v1/teacher-infos` should be at `/users/teachers` based on the route structure. The real `/api/v1/teacher-infos` route doesn't appear to exist, which explains the 404 error. `/lessons` works because it's registered as a sub-router. `/stadiums`, `/payments` work. So the actual API structure is different from what the documentation suggests—the routes are nested under `/users` for students and teachers, while lessons, stadiums, and payments are top-level endpoints. The 404s make sense now: `/students` returns 404 because there are only routes for `/students/register` and `/students/:id`, and `/teacher-infos` doesn't exist as a direct endpoint at all.","thinkingSignature":"9da3efa17f11fd137a33a0543bd2f0d4774e452806e6eb36af1a7726538a337e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bgctyfzpl5st_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << PYEOF\nimport json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\ntoken = open(\"/tmp/dtlx_token.txt\").read().strip()\n\ntests = [\n    # Actual working paths\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/users/role\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/users/teachers\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/users/students\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/users/sales\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/users/leads\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/roles\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/agents\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/courses\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/lessons\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/vehicles\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/stadiums\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/payments\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/notify-configs\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/notify-contents\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/work-calendars\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/student-infos\", True),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/exams\", True),\n    # Public endpoints\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/guests\", False),\n    (\"POST\", \"/api/v1/guests/register\", False),\n]\n\nfor method, path, auth in tests:\n    try:\n        req = urllib.request.Request(f\"http://localhost:5555{path}\", method=method)\n        if auth:\n            req.add_header(\"Authorization\", f\"Bearer {token}\")\n        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5)\n        rd = json.loads(resp.read())\n        if isinstance(rd.get(\"data\"), list):\n            print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | {len(rd['data'])} items\")\n        elif isinstance(rd.get(\"data\"), dict):\n            d2 = rd[\"data\"]\n            if \"docs\" in d2: print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | {len(d2['docs'])} items\")\n            elif \"doc\" in d2: print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | 1 doc\")\n            elif \"result\" in d2: print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | result={len(d2['result'])} items\")\n            else: print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | keys={list(d2.keys())[:4]}\")\n        elif \"status\" in rd and resp.status == 200:\n            print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status} | msg={rd.get('message','')[:30]}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"✅ {path}: {resp.status}\")\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        body = e.read().decode()[:100]\n        print(f\"❌ {path}: {e.code} → {body}\")\n    except Exception as ex:\n        print(f\"❌ {path}: {ex}\")\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":379,"output":1185,"cacheRead":92375,"cacheWrite":537,"totalTokens":94476,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776140012622,"responseId":"062cf1ee16c7466fd5aa9914caf55fb0"}}
