{"type":"message","id":"eb5704a0","parentId":"86eef585","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:14:17.658Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The guests.route.js has `router.post('/')` which should match POST `/guests`. But earlier when I tested GET `/api/v1/guests`, it worked with 200. Now POST `/api/v1/guests/register` returns 401.\n\nWait, the issue is that the request I sent was to `/api/v1/guests/register`, but the guests.route doesn't have a `/register` path! It only has:\n- `POST /` → register a guest\n- `POST /leads` → register a lead\n- `GET /` → list guests\n- `GET /:id` → get guest by ID\n\n\n- etc.\n\nSo `/guests/register` is a 404 because there's no such route, but the 401 response means the auth middleware is blocking it before it even gets to that point. Let me trace through what happens when a request hits `/guests/register` — the auth middleware should be skipped for public routes, but something's not matching up. Actually, I should test this with a valid registration payload to see what the actual response is.","thinkingSignature":"71bc3976afb544c702a0b3f9c10a86fef463e19a27a709396ebb1719e19984ae"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4bpjok8p9z9k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << PYEOF\nimport json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\n# Test guest register - POST to /guests (correct path)\ndata = json.dumps({\n    \"first_name\": \"Test\",\n    \"last_name\": \"Guest\",\n    \"phone\": \"0909000001\",\n    \"email\": \"test@example.com\"\n}).encode()\n\ntests = [\n    (\"POST\", \"/api/v1/guests\", False, data),\n    (\"GET\", \"/api/v1/guests\", False, None),\n]\n\nfor method, path, auth, body in tests:\n    try:\n        req = urllib.request.Request(f\"http://localhost:5555{path}\", data=body, method=method, headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"})\n        if auth:\n            req.add_header(\"Authorization\", f\"Bearer {open('/tmp/dtlx_token.txt').read().strip()}\")\n        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5)\n        rd = json.loads(resp.read())\n        print(f\"✅ {method} {path}: {resp.status} | {json.dumps(rd, ensure_ascii=False)[:150]}\")\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        body_err = e.read().decode()[:100]\n        print(f\"❌ {method} {path}: {e.code} → {body_err}\")\n    except Exception as ex:\n        print(f\"❌ {method} {path}: {ex}\")\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":273,"output":553,"cacheRead":93189,"cacheWrite":1922,"totalTokens":95937,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776140045343,"responseId":"062cf20e0b321ae4fe4f29ffa92652d1"}}
